entries.meaning: The lack of the quality of resolve.
examples: But the truth is that all of us, including this Union, are now poised at a dangerous place midst the unresolve of God that flows off as unresolve into the real world around us.

verbs.description: unresolve (third-person singular simple present unresolves, present participle unresolving, simple past and past participle unresolved)
